episodes.title: #fotodaily Episode 1, June 17, 2015: "The BIG social media strategy is a myth"
episodes.description:
This is the first episode of a short form podcast about my work as an event photographer, video journalist, and social media content creator.

In this episode, I discuss the "mythical" big social media strategy that many small companies think they need before venturing onto social media. I offer some ideas on making a smaller and more manageable strategy that's easier to maintain based on sharing what a company does daily using one of the most powerful media tools that most of us already own: a smartphone.

Comments or questions welcome. Here or via Twitter: 
@fotobygreg #fotodaily #audiomo

episodes.title: #personaldaily #audiomo, June 17, 2015: The Link Between Entrepreneurship and Depression
episodes.description:
I am starting out recording a #personaldaily as part of #audiomo this month. In this one I expand on the idea I mentioned in yesterday's recording about the link between entrepreneurship and depression.

I mention a few links/articles:
http://www.inc.com/magazine/201309/jessica-bruder/psychological-price-of-entrepreneurship.html

http://www.amazon.com/The-Hypomanic-Edge-Between-Craziness/dp/0743243455

And the documentary I refer to with Stephen Fry is entitled, "The Secret Life of the Manic Depressive".

What makes you happy?

Can you tell us your name?
